A baby’s body was found at the Newcastle landfill site in KwaZulu-Natal earlier today, May 23, Newcastle Advertiser reports.
According to eyewitnesses at the scene, the baby was discovered early morning by one of the recycling workers.
READ MORE: Newborn baby boy found dead at dumping site in Phalaborwa

The body of a baby covered in maggots and flies was found dumped at the Newcastle Landfill.
One of the workers, known as Lucky, explained the baby was found in a plastic refuse bag.
Officials have not yet arrived on the scene, and further investigations are pending.
